        "subject": "LU-17242 libcfs: implement LUSTRE_TRACE",
        "message": "LU-17242 libcfs: implement LUSTRE_TRACE\n\nImplement the LUSTRE_TRACE macro which automatically\nlogs the entry and exit of a function to the Lustre\ndebug log. To enable this, backport the cleanup.h\nheader from the Linux kernel.\n\nThe legacy ENTRY/RETURN macros are inconsistently used\nand prone to error; most often, developers will forget\nto annotate all entry and exit points for the function.\n\nReplace two incorrect uses of ENTRY with LUSTRE_TRACE.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nTest-Parameters: fortestonly\nSigned-off-by: Timothy Day <timday@amazon.com>\nChange-Id: I1008d7c770bd98155a6ab07efa30d0ce1c1f91bc\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
